Expanded tests/issues-tests.el from 12 to 48 tests with robust coverage.

New tests added:
- issue-parse-line edge cases: zero comments, high count, empty status, garbage input, index always 0
- issue-parse-comment: message-id extraction, date-string format, zero-padding
- issues-timestamp-to-iso: zero-padding edge case
- issues-make-sort-key: issue itself (index 0), last comment (index=count), ordering correctness across issues and comments
- issues-compare-numeric: basic numeric string comparison
- issue-get-line: returns nil for missing ID
- issue-get-comment: first post (index 0) content
- issue-comment-count: correct counts for all three example issues
- issue-comments: excludes first post, correct indices
- issue-chain: correct entry counts, sequential indices, parsed dates
- issue-chain-raw: sequential indices starting at 0
- issue-last-updated: returns newest date for multi-comment and no-comment issues
- issue-all-details: status propagation, empty descriptions for comments, non-empty for issues, sort ordering, comment-count propagation
- issues-root-directory and issues-issue-directory: correct path construction
- issues-read-message-id: middle segment extraction for comments and first post
- issues-file-map: correct entry count and structure
- issues-append-sort-key: adds sort-key while preserving existing fields
- list-issues: buffer creation, mode, entry count, 7 columns per entry
- Mode definitions and keybindings

Also fixed a bug in the mock: warbo-issues-mock-insert-file-contents was using wrong index to extract issue-id from path (off by one due to /new/ subdirectory in path).
